sss - simple scripting for scala

sss lets you write simple standalone scripts in Scala that incorporate
Maven dependencies.  For example:


helloworld.sss
#!/usr/bin/sss

@library("slf4j")
@library("org.scalaz" %% "scalaz" % "0.12")

import slf4s._

object Hello extends App {
  log("hello world")
}

You can then execute helloworld.sss by making it executable and entering ./helloworld.sss
at the 
